law.text:
In addition to the powers and duties set forth elsewhere in this title, the Board has the following powers and duties:
To adopt rules and regulations to carry out the provisions of this title;
To adopt and publish codes of ethics for the practices of audiology, hearing aid dispensing, and speech-language pathology, and the assistance in the practice of speech-language pathology;
To adopt an official seal;
To hold hearings and keep records and minutes necessary for the orderly conduct of business;
To issue a list annually of the names of all individuals licensed by the Board;
To send any notice that the Board is required to give to a licensee under this title to the last known address given to the Board by the licensee; and
To adopt regulations governing the use of telehealth communications by audiologists, hearing aid dispensers, and speech-language pathologists.
